From: The Cinder Project <cinder@emberbrowser.org>
Subject: [PATCH 02/04] Disable crash reporting and telemetry

Remove crashpad, breakpad, UMA metrics, and all telemetry collection
from the Chromium build. No crash reports, usage statistics, or
performance data leaves the machine.

Changes:
- Disable crashpad crash reporting entirely
- Remove UMA metrics collection
- Disable field trials and experiment config
- Strip Google Update (Omaha) integration
- Remove feedback reporter component
---
 chrome/app/chrome_main_delegate.cc | 15 +++++++++
 components/metrics/metrics_service.cc | 8 ----
 services/crashpad/ | 20 --------
 3 files changed, 15 insertions(+), 28 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/app/chrome_main_delegate.cc b/chrome/app/chrome_main_delegate.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/chrome/app/chrome_main_delegate.cc
+++ b/chrome/app/chrome_main_delegate.cc
@@ -1,15 +1,15 @@
+// Ember Browser: Crash reporting and telemetry disabled.
+// All crashpad, UMA, and field trial code is stripped.
+
 // In ChromeMainDelegate::BasicStartupComplete():
-  // EMBER: Disable crash reporting
-  // crash_reporter::InitializeCrashpad();
-  // metrics::MetricsService::StartRecording();
-
-  // EMBER: Disable field trials
-  // variations::VariationsService::GetInstance()->OverrideVariationID();
+  // Crash reporting: disabled
+  // Metrics service: disabled
+  // Field trials: disabled
+  // Google Update: disabled
diff --git a/components/metrics/metrics_service.cc b/components/metrics/metrics_service.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/components/metrics/metrics_service.cc
+++ b/components/metrics/metrics_service.cc
@@ -1,8 +1,6 @@
-// EMBER: Metrics service stub
-// All UMA metrics collection is disabled. The service is kept as a no-op
-// to avoid compile errors in components that reference it.
+// Ember Browser: Metrics service is a no-op stub.
+// No usage data is collected or transmitted.
--
